<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-244-026  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 244 026.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  April 1990 v8 n4 p86(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>R:base loosens up. (Software Review) (R:base 3.0) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bott, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microrim Corp's R:base 3.0 has many new user-interface andquerying features designed to let it compete with Borland'sParadox.andP;  The new package replaces the command line with a seriesof pull-down menus and mouse support.andP;  New form-design featuresinclude auto-numbering fields, a 'skip' option for moving to theirfields, and pop-up windows that users can customize to display andselect data from any table.andP;  Query by example (QBE) allows theuser to select rows from any table and sort or modify theresulting output.andP;  R:base's QBE editing features are superior tothose of Paradox, and the new version features a sophisticatedband-oriented report writer.andP;  It supports over 100 printers andincorporates a re-written command structure that conforms toStructured Query Language (SQL).andP;  Microrim promises directfront-end SQL support in the next R:base release.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microrim Inc. (products).andO;Product:   R:base 3.0 (Data base management system).andO;Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsEvaluationUser InterfaceSoftware Packages.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Snapshot. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>